dc_title_s: Tacloban, Philippine Islands, Leyte Province, Leyte. A.M.S. S901
dc_description_s: AMS 3. Alternate title: Tacloban. In upper left margin: Philippine city plans 1:5,500 (approx.). Polyconic projection. Relief shown by form lines and spot elevation.Compiled from USC&GS Topographic Field Survey Sheets, 1:20,000, P14A, 1901; USC&GS Chart No. 4464, 1:30,000, 1910 (Special printing, 43-8/18); Map of Tacloban, 1:5,040, 1904; Development plan of Tacloban, 1:2,000, Director of Public Works, 1928. Vertical mosaic, 1:20,000, prior to 1940; vertical photograph, prior to 1940.
dc_publisher_s: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1944.
